[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

With 24 points you open 2\C. Partner responds 2\H.  

Partner has 8+ points and a good 5-card \H suit. Your hand has revalued to 25 points. You are forced to game but you don't want to bid it yet since you have slam in mind. So you temporize by showing your \H support. Partner bids 4\H. What do say? 

You bid 4NT, asking for Aces. Partner replies 5\D. What now? 

You now say 6\H and lay down a great dummy.}

